            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "We ship a treesitter markdown parser but don't enable it by default, yet. I keep forgetting the reason, but we eventually will enable it. Like this: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/198c9e9bca7549cf7110be8c6f1df1c38d4e747f/runtime/ftplugin/lua.lua#L2\n\n> but I don't see any objective reason to make this change the default for everyone.\n\nWe definitely should add a background highlight to code blocks, it looks much better, and we really under-use bg highlights. Here's how it looks with https://github.com/MeanderingProgrammer/render-markdown.nvim : \n\n<img width=\"676\" height=\"208\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b38e7b2e-fd9f-4e21-b754-281e77c67595\" />",
