            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> We ship a treesitter markdown parser but don't enable it by default, yet. I keep forgetting the reason, but we eventually will enable it. Like this: \n\nI can only guess, but I noticed that the difference in the highlighting of markdown with treesitter enabled or not is quite significant:\n\n### zaibatsu with TS off and on side by side:\n\nwhile the overall highlighting improves, some things change for the worse:\n* the heading delimiters (`#`) are not highlighted anymore\n* the URLs in the links loose their coloring too\n \nAlso, the list delimiters (`*`, etc.) change their highlighting color, which is not good or bad in particular.\n\n<img width=\"1787\" height=\"932\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c5fac88a-2bd4-4550-8df6-564e59415063\" />\n\n### default with TS of and on side by side:\n\nAs said earlier, it is already an improvement, but overall still very monochrome.\n\n<img width=\"1787\" height=\"932\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/37681a25-169f-415a-94ad-d5d30352b3bc\" />\n\ncompare it visually with a Python file using the same colorscheme. I find, it looks more vivid than the markdown file different things are easier to distinguish.\n\n<img width=\"413\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c548e6b2-662c-4658-8b83-328a46669323\" />\n",
