            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "1. The default colorscheme is _intentionally_ \"monochrome\" (and, more importantly, consistent -- there's simply not a lot of structure in Markdown files that can be captured with standard highlight groups).\n2. The other bundled colorschemes are inherited from Vim so are obviously not tuned for treesitter highlighting.\n\nLuckily, there are many, _many_, high-quality colorschemes that are just one `vim.pack.add()` away; it's also not hard to make your own. (There's also https://github.com/OXY2DEV/markview.nvim for extra-fancy Markdown viewing.)",
